Sentencas: Layered perovskite oxides with and without Ca-doped NdBa0.5Sr0.25Ca0.25Co2O5+delta (NBSCaCO) and NdBa0.5Sr0.25Ca0.25Co2O5+delta (NBSCO) are studied to investigate the effects of Ca doping on the crystal structure, thermal behavior, electrical and electrochemical properties.
Titulo: Investigation of layered perovskite NdBa0.5Sr0.25Ca0.25Co2O5+δ as cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Both NBSCO and NBSCaCO are tetragonal structure with P4/mmm space group.
Titulo: Investigation of layered perovskite NdBa0.5Sr0.25Ca0.25Co2O5+δ as cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The average thermal expansion coefficient (TEC) value is reduced from 23.3 x 10(-6) K-1 to 19.8 x 10(-6) K-1 during 30-800 degrees C.
Titulo: Investigation of layered perovskite NdBa0.5Sr0.25Ca0.25Co2O5+δ as cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrical conductivities are increased by Ca doping.
Titulo: Investigation of layered perovskite NdBa0.5Sr0.25Ca0.25Co2O5+δ as cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Both electrical conductivities of NBSCO and NBSCaCO are higher than 600 S.cm(-1) over 30-800 degrees C. Substitution of Sr with Ca can effectively improve the electrochemical properties of NBSCaCO.
Titulo: Investigation of layered perovskite NdBa0.5Sr0.25Ca0.25Co2O5+δ as cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: From 650 degrees C to 800 degrees C, the area specific resistance (ASR) of NBSCaCO are decreased from 0.62 to 0.062 Omega cm(2) and the corresponding output power density are increased from 258 to 812 mW cm(-2).
Titulo: Investigation of layered perovskite NdBa0.5Sr0.25Ca0.25Co2O5+δ as cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: On the basis of these results, Ca doped layered perovskite NBSCaCO can be a good cathode candidate material for SOFC application.
Titulo: Investigation of layered perovskite NdBa0.5Sr0.25Ca0.25Co2O5+δ as cathode for solid oxide fuel cells
